column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Cloudy , Light Rain , Moderate Wind Swirling/Variable
column13: Clear control, water pumping from gauge pool.
column14: FT2 wade upstream around the corner. Near two exposed rocks. Some angled flow at left bank. Curve info will not populate in eHSN. @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Water pump running beside gauge, drawing water from gauge pool at gauge. Water level in OTT experiencing small fluctuations from pumping. Water levels showing large changes due to pumping and surge as a result of pumping. First water level taken close to gauge and likely affected by draw-down from the water pump. Second and third water levels taken closer to OTT, away from pumping, assumed more valid. Logger reading 3 minutes fast due to failed GPS. Downloaded record back to prior visit and reset HG and clock for 15:20. Reset took for 15:30. Power cycled logger at 15:50, as replacing GPS could still not get fixed time. No stage recorded from 15:50 to 16:05 due to power cycling. No record from 16:20 to 16:40 due to firmware update. Reset logger to found DWL after firmware update. Logger was reading high, likely due to the surging caused by the water pump in the gauge pool. Mid-section

column14: @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ Good measurement, left bank had small gravel bar, too low to measure, minimal flow through. Otherwise good measurement. Did not reset logger. DWL from primary. Stage was changing over time, and a large diesel pump was pulling water directly at the orifice for the water treatment plant. Checked cut at 12:40, no change to cut, despite surging water, bubbler reading within 0.003m at 12:40. Chose not to apply SRC due to influence of surge and water pump. EST SRC based on found SRC may be required for previous record. When downloading record found that logger had hour and minute correct, but was logging for July 29th 2023. Corrected logger date/time settings after downloading data to logger file. Clock reset at 12:49. Clock drift adjustment will likely be required. Uncertain when the invalid month was input to the logger. Past LG files may note when this occurred. Mid-section
